For those considering attending the forthcoming Bioconductor Developers' meeting in Tokyo (see announcement below), there are a number of travel scholarships (up to $400 USD each) for students and package developers to help cover the cost of travel to attend the meeting.

To apply for a scholarship, please submit a brief statement (200 words or less) describing your interest in the meeting. If you are a package developer or maintainer please tell us the package(s) you work on. The due date for applications is Friday 21st August.

Email applications to gustin.s at wehi.edu.au and include SCHOLARSHIP in the subject line.

Best wishes,

Matt

