From dtenenba at fredhutch.org  Fri Aug 21 20:14:00 2015
From: dtenenba at fredhutch.org (Dan Tenenbaum)
Date: Fri, 21 Aug 2015 11:14:00 -0700 (PDT)
Subject: [Bioc-devel] Windows build error: cannot open file
 'C:\Users\pkgbuild\AppData\Local\Temp\RtmpaEUpE0\xshell23645160444e':
 Permission denied
In-Reply-To: <D1FCB7AC.EA4%Simon.Coetzee@cshs.org>
Message-ID: <87971635.1088168.1440180840099.JavaMail.root@fredhutch.org>

Often these kind of permission issues on windows have to do with using parallel resources and not cleaning up properly. It sometimes doesn't matter on other OSes, but windows is particular about it. For example, if you start a socket cluster, you must close it when you are done using it.

Dan


